The print CommandÂ¶

print, print the value of parameters:

print [ -l | -s ] parameter [ -l | -s ] parameter ...

Print the value of a scalar (-s, default) or list (-l) parameters. With the -s option, the value is first converted to a string which gives the normal representation of value (list values are enclosed in square brackers, e.g.,d:

ZBTest> print path
[/home/mrohan/xmpl/test-area, /home/mrohan/bin, /usr/bin, /bin]
ZBTest> print _platform
unix

With the -l option, the value is printed as a list. If the parameter is not a list, it’’s value is first converted to a list. E.g.,:

ZBTest> print -l l1
ZBTest> print _platform
unix
ZBTest> print -l _platform
1) "unix"
ZBTest> print -l path
1) "/home/mrohan/xmpl/test-area"
2) "/home/mrohan/bin"
3) "/usr/bin"
4) "/bin"
